300 319 43 (1. ) 75 SB
375 319 1713 (The new model is not described in the working paper.  Adding such a description would be a difficult) 1713 SB
375 369 1713 (and time consuming process \(in Tokyo, the core-3 group spent several hours discussing aspects of the) 1713 SB
375 419 1667 (new model that must be described in the Working Paper, but this did not even give rise to any firm) 1667 SB
375 469 1573 (proposals for how the issues should be addressed, and certainly not Working Paper wording\).) 1573 SB
300 519 43 (2. ) 75 SB
375 519 1506 (The new model is radically different than existing implementations and it has never been) 1506 SB
375 569 231 (implemented.) 231 SB
300 619 43 (3. ) 75 SB
375 619 1722 (Instantiations occur in a synthesized context, which makes it much harder for users to understand and) 1722 SB
375 669 762 (correct errors that occur during instantiation.) 762 SB
300 719 43 (4. ) 75 SB
375 719 1686 (The compilation model requires context merging  \(which some choose to describe as a name lookup) 1686 SB
375 769 1676 (process that  considers multiple contexts\).  Context merging is a complex process that is difficult to) 1676 SB
375 819 382 (specify \(see #5 below\).) 382 SB
300 869 43 (5. ) 75 SB
375 869 1332 (The compilation model cannot be implemented efficiently enough to be usable.) 1332 SB
300 969 1785 (The existence of all of these problems has been acknowledged even by those who continue to advocate the) 1785 SB
300 1019 1758 (new compilation model \(although, of course, they may disagree about the severity and importance of the) 1758 SB
300 1069 1793 (problems\), but no significant progress has been made in resolving any of them.  In over a year no progress) 1793 SB
300 1119 1782 (has been made in incorporating a description of the new model in the Working Paper, and no attempt has) 1782 SB
300 1169 1449 (been made to describe an implementation that would provide acceptable performance.) 1449 SB
32 0 0 58 58 0 0 0 53 /Helvetica-Bold /font13 ANSIFont font
300 1269 64 (2. ) 78 SB
378 1269 328 (Alternatives) 328 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 1351 1713 (The committee is trying to send out the second CD.  For this to be done, all significant changes to the) 1713 SB
300 1401 1595 (Working Paper must be completed.  Certainly, this includes describing the compilation model.) 1595 SB
300 1451 656 (The alternatives for the committee are:) 656 SB
300 1551 43 (1. ) 75 SB
375 1551 1579 (Stick with the new compilation model and take the time to work out the remaining issues and) 1579 SB
375 1601 1559 (describe the model in the Working Paper.  Hopefully this process would include producing a) 1559 SB
375 1651 1724 (document that describes how the performance problems of the new model can be addressed.  Based on) 1724 SB
375 1701 1678 (the rate of progress at the last meeting, it would probably take at least 2-3 meetings to get this work) 1678 SB
375 1751 981 (done \(with the added cost of not getting other work done\).) 981 SB
300 1801 43 (2. ) 75 SB
375 1801 1426 (Adopt an alternate model that codifies existing practice, and can be described easily.) 1426 SB
300 1901 964 (I believe the time has come to choose an alternate model.) 964 SB
32 0 0 58 58 0 0 0 53 /Helvetica-Bold /font13 ANSIFont font
300 2001 64 (3. ) 78 SB
378 2001 871 (Proposal for an Alternate Model) 871 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 2083 1709 (The template compilation model adopted in Valley Forge was intended to permit two different source) 1709 SB
300 2133 1720 (organizations: the one in which templates are defined in separate translation units, and the commonly) 1720 SB
300 2183 1705 (used model in which templates are explicitly included in the translation units in which they are used.) 1705 SB
300 2233 1765 (This proposal is to retain only the model in which the templates are explicitly included in the translation) 1765 SB
300 2283 1650 (units in which they are used \(sometimes called the \223include everything\224 model\).  This model is in) 1650 SB
300 2333 1713 (widespread use.  It is easy to understand and use.  Although it is sometimes criticized for its cost, it is) 1713 SB
300 2383 1771 (much less expensive than the separate compilation model, and techniques for optimizing this method are) 1771 SB
300 2433 635 (well understood and widely deployed.) 635 SB
300 2483 1746 (The model eliminates the need to do context merging and, as a result, eliminates the need to define and) 1746 SB
300 2533 1738 (describe the context merging process.  Instead of context merging it makes use of textual inclusion, the) 1738 SB
300 2583 971 (rules for which are already present in the working  paper.) 971 SB
